<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.342/–: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 20,
                                        1926—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>13. Legation’s cable No. 12, October 5, 5 p.m. Department is pleased to
                            learn that the Foreign Minister is favorably disposed towards
                            negotiating a treaty. A draft of the treaty and instructions are being
                            prepared and will go forward shortly by pouch.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>